article.headline: Marquette 63, South Florida 52
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Lazar Hayward scored 18 points to lead Marquette to a 63-52 victory over South Florida in Big East Conference play on Saturday. Hayward added 14 rebounds, as Marquette (16-8, 7-5) won its fifth straight. Jimmy Butler had 15 points and Maurice Acker added 14, as Marquette won despite getting outrebounded 42-30. Dominique Jones, the Big East's third-leading scorer at 21.9 points per game, had 16 to lead South Florida (15-9, 5-7) but made just 6 of 21 from the field. Marquette led 31-27 at halftime and opened the second half on an 18-8 run, including eight points from David Cubillan, to take a 49-35 lead. South Florida got no closer than six the rest of the way and shot just 29.7 percent in the second half. The Bulls made 4 of 20 three-pointers in the game.
